 |archive-date=2022-03-11 |access-date=2022-03-11 |website=Bounding Into Comics}}</ref><ref name="cbc cinemablend">{{cite news |last=Weaver |first=Jackson |date=March 8, 2022 |title=Turning Red is for everyone, cast says after review calls film about Chinese-Canadian girl unrelatable |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/entertainment/turning-red-review-pulled-1.6377614 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220312164102/https://www.cbc.ca/news/entertainment/turning-red-review-pulled-1.6377614 |archive-date=2022-03-12 |work=[[CBC.ca|CBC.ca]] |accessdate=March 12, 2022}}</ref>。《[[娱乐週刊|娱乐週刊]]》编辑针对此事评论「网路有记忆，道歉无法抹煞种族歧视的不当言词」，指称「这不是初级小编犯的错误，这代表一家媒体负责人的立场，那这种媒体还能看吗？」<ref>{{cite web |title=CinemaBlend Pulls Review Of Turning Red After Social Media Accuses Author Of Sexism And Racism Over Opinion That He Was “Not The Film’s Target Audience” |url=https://boundingintocomics.com/2022/03/11/cinemablend-pulls-review-of-turning-red-after-social-media-accuses-author-of-sexism-and-racism-over-opinion-that-he-was-not-the-films-target-audience/|url-status=live |archive-url=https://boundingintocomics.com/2022/03/11/cinemablend-pulls-review-of-turning-red-after-social-media-accuses-author-of-sexism-and-racism-over-opinion-that-he-was-not-the-films-target-audience/|archive-date=2022-03-11 |access-date=2022-03-11 |website=Bounding Into Comics}}</ref>。

